other_tests.findings: Lower chest shows bibasilar atelectasis, no pleural or pericardial effusion. Abdomen shows a 6 mm hypodensity in the left hepatic lobe, likely a cyst, hemangioma, or biliary hamartoma. The appendix is dilated with wall hyperemia and moderate surrounding fat stranding, with marked wall edema/phlegmon at the base. No evidence of drainable fluid collection or bowel obstruction. Remaining organs are unremarkable.
